# Foundation rules live in AGENTS.md

Cursor reads `AGENTS.md` at the repo root natively. The full project body
(guardrails, environments, voice rules, stack defaults) is THERE and is not
repeated here. Read `AGENTS.md` first.

This file exists only to show the one thing a Cursor `.mdc` rule adds over the
cross-tool standard: a path-scoped override. Use a separate, narrowly scoped
`.mdc` file (its own `globs`) when a subtree needs an extra rule that does not
belong in the global body. Do not copy the shared body into any `.mdc` file.

## Scoped-override sample (delete or adapt; illustrative only)

A real scoped rule would live in its own file such as
`.cursor/rules/20-migrations.mdc` with `alwaysApply: false` and `globs` limited
to the relevant subtree, so it loads only when those files are in context:

    ---
    description: Supabase migration files are append-only.
    globs:
      - "supabase/migrations/**"
    alwaysApply: false
    ---
    Migrations are append-only. Never edit a migration that has run against any
    shared environment; add a new timestamped migration instead. One migration
    set serves every environment. See AGENTS.md.
